text: Osage City High School is a public high school in Osage City, Kansas, United States. It is a part of Unified School District 420. ==Athletics== ===Teams=== Osage City's athletic teams are nicknamed the Indians and the school's colors are red and white. Osage City teams compete in the following sports: *Football *Golf *Baseball *Softball *Basketball *Track *Cross country *Volleyball ===State championships=== *Boys basketball **2016 Kansas 3A State Championshttp://www.och-c.com/?q=article/indians-carry-no-1-state-championship ==Demographics== 88% of the student population at Osage City High School identify as Caucasian, 1% identify as African American, 2% identify as American Indian/Alaskan Native, 0.5% identify as Asian, 3% identify as Hispanic, and 5% identify as multiracial.https://www.usnews.com/education/best-high- schools/kansas/districts/osage-city/osage-city-high-8109/student-body The student body makeup is 48% male and 52% female. ==Notable alumni== *Blake Treinen, MLB player for the Oakland Athleticshttps://www.cjonline.com/sports/2016-05-01/national-treasure-treinen- overcomes-various-hurdles-gain-big-league-spot ==References== ==External links== * Category:Public high schools in Kansas
